HEADWORD: Revertent
<hw>Re*vert"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A remedy which restores the natural order of the inverted
irritative motions in the animal system.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>E. Darwin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

